vs-earth-map-creator
============================
Make cool earth maps in Vintage Story (VS)

Requirements
-------------------
dotnet 8
vintage story
gdal
python3
imagemagick

Directories
-------------------
.
├── CakeBuild         - build
├── EarthMapCreator   - vs code mod
└── Geo               - geospatial processing scripts

Usage
-------------------
under Geo/ run pip install -r requirements.txt
then, set the desired map resolution and long/lat bounds under Geo/scripts/config_map.sh
run launch.sh from the Geo directory (sh ./scripts/launch.sh)
some bitmap files will be output to work/build

the vintage story mod takes these bitmap files and overrides the vanilla generation.
these bitmap files should go into the config directory (~/.config/VintagestoryData/EarthMap/)

current generation only supports multiples of 512 (vintage story region size)
set the size of the map as appropriate under ModConfig/EarthMapCreator.json

create a world, then run the command /earthmap generate.
the map is generated where chunk 0,0 (top left of the world) is the top left of the map.

Limitations/TODO
-------------------
- Map generation must be a multiple of 512 blocks.
- Much more data is missing that can be applied to VS (i.e. rock strata, ores)
- Vintage Story - map resolutions/padding are hardcoded on the client
- Alot of values are hardcoded
See ./TODO for a more comprehensive list

Data Used/Acknowledgments
-------------------
- GMTED 250m DEM: https://edcintl.cr.usgs.gov/downloads/sciweb1/shared/topo/downloads/GMTED/Grid_ZipFiles/ds75_grd.zip
- GEBCO 2025 (bathymetry): https://www.gebco.net/
- OpenStreetMap: https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright
- Natural Earth: https://www.naturalearthdata.com/
- WorldClim: https://www.worldclim.org/data/worldclim21.html
- Reverse engineered existing Minecraft map programs, EarthTiles, earthtomc, worldpainter

